    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Output Shaft and Rear Bearing Assemblies</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the output shaft forward and through the rear bearing
                assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018c1">Figure 121</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018c1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018c1" filename="../figg13/G13018c1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 121. Drive Output Shaft Forward and Through Rear Bearing Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When applying force to the rear of the output shaft, DO NOT DAMAGE THE THREADS. Support the
                        front of the shaft to avoid damaging the mainshaft quill once the output shaft is free of the
                        bearing assembly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
